I want my colleagues to know that I'm not suggesting this be done any time soon. In fact, it seems safer to me if this never happens at all. Still, I'd be remiss if I didn't submit this proposal so it was at least on the books.

I highly suggest this IS NOT done, to prevent damaging our relationship with SCP-073. Further, something like this may end up being a "Irresistible Force/Immovable Rock" scenario, which could introduce substantial Euclid elements to the testing.

Proposal: SCP-073 and SCP-053 both seem to posses substantial "responsive" defense systems to physical harm. This proposal suggests that SCP-073 be exposed to SCP-053's emotional effect field, and that SCP-073 be allowed to harm her.







